FileGlue is a nodejs module for splitting files into smaller chunks, and then reconstructing them again. In the process,
there should be no changes to the contents of the file.

API

var fileGlue = require('fileGlue');

fileGlue.glue(filePaths, outputFilePath, callback)
  filePaths: Array of file paths, in order, that will be combined to create the end file
  outputFilePath: Location to output the generated file
  callback: Called after completion as "callback (error)"

fileGlue.tear(filePath, tearSize, callback)
  filePath: File to tear apart
  tearSize: Specifies the maximum size, in bytes, of the generated files
  callback: Call after completion as "callback (error)"
